HEADWORD: Chasteness
<hw>Chaste"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Chastity; purity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Literature & Art)</fld> <def>Freedom from all that
is meretricious, gaudy, or affected; <as>as, <ex>chasteness</ex> of
design</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chastisable</ent>⟦br⟧
